 for bestpractices and # Dashboard

## Overview
This prompt drives the creation of a full-featured Dashboard experience for PulseBoard — a single-company health analysis platform. The Dashboard is the primary workspace that surfaces the user’s current company health, latest AI-generated analyses, quick actions, and guided paths to improve data completeness and run analyses. If no company exists, the Dashboard should display a prominent CTA to set up the company via the Create Company wizard. The implementation must respect dependency-first sequencing: auth/access control and core data setup must be completed before dashboard/workspace/analytics tasks.

The solution must be end-to-end, covering frontend, backend, and integrations. It should enforce runtime safety rules (null/undefined guards for arrays, proper initial states, validated API shapes) and be designed for scalable, maintainable code. Emphasize performance via caching, efficient search, and resilient integrations.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Dashboard page is the primary workspace focused on the user’s single company. It surfaces the company health at-a-glance, latest AI-generated analyses, quick actions, and guided steps to improve data completeness and run analyses. If no company exists, show an empty-state with a clear CTA to set up the company.

Goals:
- Provide a cohesive, single-company focused cockpit with quick visibility into health and key metrics, recent analyses, and actionable next steps. Integrate with connected features (Caching, Search, Integrations, Health Scoring, AI Analysis, Reports, Notifications) to deliver a fast, actionable experience.

Features connected:
- Caching & Performance: Cache computed results, external integration responses, and frequently used data to reduce latency and API costs.
- Search & Filter: Full-text search and filters for companies, reports, and users, with autosuggest and performance optimization.
- Integrations & Connectors: Connectors to fetch financials and analytics from QuickBooks, Google Analytics, LinkedIn pages, Stripe, and CSV upload. Handles OAuth, credential storage, and periodic syncs.
- Health Scoring Engine: Computes overall company health and sub-scores (financial, market, brand/social) using weighted rules and optional benchmarking against industry norms.
- Report Export / PDF Generation: Server-side PDF generation for exporting AI reports with branding options and queued processing for large exports.
- AI Analysis Engine: Orchestrates AI prompts to generate executive summary, SWOT, financial/market/social analysis, risks, opportunities, and prioritized action plan. Supports depth levels and optional benchmarks.
- Notifications & Emails: Transactional and in-app notifications for completed analyses, export ready, failed jobs, billing, and admin alerts. Uses email provider and in-app inbox.

UI elements and guidance:
- Top bar: App title, current company name, search reports, notifications, profile menu.
- Company header card: Company name, industry, overall health score, last analysis date, quick financial snapshot (monthly revenue, profit, cash).
- Primary action buttons: Generate Analysis, Edit Company, Export Report (PDF), Replace / Delete Company (settings).
- Health breakdown cards: Financial score, Market score, Brand/Social score with mini-trend sparkline and recommended next action.
- Latest Analysis / Executive Summary card: Quick view with large “Regenerate” CTA.
- Data completeness meter: Show missing fields, actionable suggestions, and quick-jump links to forms.
- Recent Reports: List scoped to current company with quick view, download, and share actions.
- Integrations & Imports tile: Connectors for QuickBooks, Google Analytics, LinkedIn, CSV import (scoped to current company).
- Tips & Next Steps: Prioritized actions based on latest analysis.
- Empty-state panel: When no company exists, CTA to set up the company via Create Company wizard.

Visual guidance:
- Follow the project design system for typography, spacing, colors, and component styling.

API integrations:
- No external API calls are mandated for this prompt; integrate with the internal APIs and connectors defined in the project context.

Project context summary (for reference):
- Target Page: Dashboard
- Single-company focus; health at-a-glance, latest analyses, quick actions, guidance, and onboarding CTA when no company exists.
- Strong emphasis on performance, data completeness, and AI-driven insights.
- Dependency-driven implementation order: auth/core data setup must be completed before dashboard.

## Components to Build
- DashboardLayout: Global layout with top bar, left/right panels, and responsive behavior.
- CompanyHeaderCard: Displays company metadata, health score, last analysis date, quick financial snapshot.
- HealthScoreCard: Displays Financial/Market/Brand scores with sparklines and recommended actions.
- AnalysisPanel: Latest Analysis / Executive Summary with view and Regenerate action.
- DataCompletenessMeter: Progress bar with missing fields and quick-jump links.
- QuickActionsBar: Primary actions (Generate Analysis, Edit Company, Export PDF, Settings).
- RecentReportsList: List of reports for current company with actions (view/download/share).
- IntegrationsTile: Scoped connectors for QuickBooks, Google Analytics, LinkedIn, CSV, with OAuth status and sync indicators.
- TipsWidget: Prioritized next steps based on latest analysis.
- EmptyStateCTA: For no-company scenario with CTA routing to Create Company wizard.
- SearchBar with autosuggest: Global search across companies, reports, and users (for dashboard or admin context).
- NotificationsInboxPanel: In-app notification center and summary indicators.
- ProfileMenu: User profile, settings, and sign-out.

Frontend details:
- Use React + TypeScript (or project’s standard stack).
- State management: useState/useEffect for local state; a global store (Redux/Context) if recommended by the team.
- Data fetching: SWR or React Query patterns (or existing data layer); ensure null-safety on all results.
- UI state defaults: Arrays as useState<Type[]>([]); ensure proper type definitions.
- Accessibility: aria-labels, keyboard navigation, readable contrast.

Backend details:
- Endpoints for dashboard data aggregation, health scoring, latest analyses, cached results, and export queue status.
- Database tables:
  - companies(id, user_id, name, industry, profile, health_score, last_analysis_at, created_at, updated_at)
  - analyses(id, company_id, type, depth_level, summary, created_at, status)
  - health_scores(id, company_id, financial_score, market_score, brand_score, overall_score, benchmark_enabled, last_updated)
  - reports(id, company_id, type, status, pdf_url, created_at)
  - integrations(id, company_id, provider, status, credentials_blob, synced_at)
  - data_completeness(id, company_id, missing_fields_json, score, updated_at)
  - cache(key, value, ttl, created_at)
  - notifications(id, user_id, type, message, read, created_at)
- Functions:
  - computeHealthScores(company_id, data) with weighted rules and optional benchmarking.
  - fetchAndCacheExternalData(company_id) coordinating connector calls with error handling.
  - generateExecutiveSummary(company_id, depth_level, benchmarks) via AI Analysis Engine.
  - exportReportPDF(report_id) with queuing support for large exports.
  - searchIndex(query, scope) with autosuggest for companies/reports/users.

Integration details:
- Implement connectors stubs for:
  - QuickBooks: OAuth flow, credentials storage, periodic sync.
  - Google Analytics: OAuth, property mapping, metrics retrieval.
  - LinkedIn Pages: OAuth, page metrics retrieval.
  - Stripe: OAuth/credential management, revenue metrics.
  - CSV Upload: file ingestion, parsing, mapping to company data.
- Ensure credential storage is secure and tokens are refreshed as needed.
- Caching strategy:
  - Cache results for computed health scores, analysis results, and frequently accessed data (e.g., recent reports) with sensible TTLs.
  - Ensure data is invalidated on relevant mutations (e.g., new analysis, updated company data, new integration sync).

UI/UX flow alignment:
- Use consistent design tokens: typography, colors, spacing, card components, grid layout.
- Provide micro-interactions: hover states, skeleton loaders, optimistic UI where appropriate.
- respect the single-company constraint: the dashboard should not show multi-company selection; the header shows the current company only, with a CTA to switch via the Create Company flow if a new company is created.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Create Dashboard page with the described layout and components.
- Implement guarded rendering for data that may be null or undefined; all arrays should be initialized to [] and guarded safely:
  - Example: const reports = data?.reports ?? [] and ensure (reports ?? []).map(...)
- Initialize state with proper defaults:
  - useState<Analyses[]>([]) for analyses lists, useState<Report[]>([]) for export/ PDFs, etc.
- Implement autosuggest search across companies, reports, and users with debounced input; display 3–5 suggestions, handle empty state gracefully.
- Implement pagination or lazy loading for RecentReportsList if needed.
- Integrate with backend APIs to fetch:
  - Current company data, health scores
  - Latest analysis data
  - Reports and export status
  - Integrations status
  - Data completeness
  - Notifications and inbox
- Ensure all API responses validate shapes:
  - const list = Array.isArray(response?.data?.list) ? response.data.list : []
- Apply optional chaining for nested objects, and default destructuring with defaults:
  - const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

### Backend
- Endpoints (examples; adapt to project routing conventions):
  - GET /api/dashboard/:companyId -> dashboardOverview
  - GET /api/companies/:companyId/health -> healthScores
  - GET /api/companies/:companyId/analyses/latest -> latestAnalyses
  - GET /api/companies/:companyId/reports -> reportsList
  - POST /api/analyses/:companyId/generate -> triggerAIAnalysis
  - POST /api/reports/:reportId/export -> queuePdfExport
  - GET /api/integrations/:companyId -> integrationsStatus
  - GET /api/cache/:key -> readCache
  - POST /api/cache/:key -> writeCache
  - POST /api/search -> searchIndex
- Data model definitions in SQL/ORM:
  - As described in Backend details above.
- Validation:
  - Validate all inputs with schema checks; guard against missing fields; return consistent error shapes.
- Security:
  - Enforce authentication (JWT/session) and authorization to ensure users access only their company data.
  - Use role-based access if applicable.
  - Protect endpoints from SQL/NoSQL injection; validate IDs and inputs.

### Integration
- Design a cohesive data flow:
  - On dashboard load, fetch current company; if none, render EmptyState with CTA.
  - OnGenerate Analysis: orchestrate AI Analysis Engine call, then update health scores, store analyses, and refresh dashboard widgets.
  - Cache per compute-heavy results; invalidate when relevant data changes.
  - Sync status indicators for integrations, and show prompts to connect if missing.
- Error handling:
  - Show non-intrusive UI error banners; retry logic for transient failures; fallback to cached data where appropriate.
  - For failed analysis or export, send notifications and emails (via Notifications & Emails feature).
- Accessibility and responsiveness:
  - Keyboard navigable, screen reader friendly.
  - Responsive grid layout for dashboards; maintain readability on mobile.

## User Experience Flow
1. User lands on Dashboard.
   - If user has no company: show EmptyStateCTA with prominent “Set up your company” button routing to Create Company wizard.
   - If a company exists: show CompanyHeaderCard with health score, last analysis date, quick metrics.
2. User views Health Breakdown: Financial, Market, Brand/Social scores with sparklines and recommended actions.
3. User taps Generate Analysis.
   - Trigger AI Analysis Engine; show loading state; on completion, refresh Latest Analysis, Health Scores, and Data Completeness metrics.
   - Notify user via in-app notification and optional email if configured.
4. User uses Quick Actions:
   - Edit Company: open Create/Update Company wizard with prefilled data.
   - Export PDF: queue server-side export; show status and download link when ready.
   - Settings: access to Replace/Delete Company (respect single-company constraint).
5. User views Recent Reports: quick view, download, and share actions; search across reports via top search bar.
6. Integrations tile shows current company integrations status; connect new connectors or view sync history.
7. Tips widget guides user to complete missing fields and run analyses; actions jump to corresponding forms.
8. If user signs out or switches user, profile menu handles routing accordingly.

## Build Order & Dependencies (Mandatory)
- Prerequisites:
  - Authentication system in place (login flows, session management).
  - Core data models for Company, Analyses, Reports, HealthScores, Integrations, Notifications, and Users.
  - Basic API layer to fetch dashboard-related data.
- Blocks:
  - Dashboard UI cannot be completed until health scoring engine and AI analysis engine endpoints exist.
  - Integrations cannot be fully demonstrated without OAuth flows, credential storage, and periodic syncs in place.
- Sequencing Rule:
  - Auth/access control and core data setup must be completed before dashboard/workspace/analytics pages when both exist.

