API Endpoints (Routes and Methods):
- GET /api/dashboard/:companyId -> dashboardOverview
- GET /api/companies/:companyId/health -> healthScores
- GET /api/companies/:companyId/analyses/latest -> latestAnalyses
- GET /api/companies/:companyId/reports -> reportsList
- POST /api/analyses/:companyId/generate -> triggerAIAnalysis
- POST /api/reports/:reportId/export -> queuePdfExport
- GET /api/integrations/:companyId -> integrationsStatus
- GET /api/cache/:key -> readCache
- POST /api/cache/:key -> writeCache
- POST /api/search -> searchIndex

Security:
- Authentication: session-based or JWT; all dashboard endpoints require valid session.
- Authorization: ensure user owns the company; enforce single-company constraint for setup flows.
- Data validation: use schema validation on all inputs; sanitize outputs.
- Secrets/credentials: store OAuth tokens securely; refresh as needed; never expose credentials in client code.

Validation:
- All API responses validated; shapes normalized to arrays when applicable:
  - const list = Array.isArray(response?.data?.list) ? response.data.list : []
- Optional chaining and default values used consistently.
- Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

UI/UX Guidelines:
- Align with design system tokens; ensure consistency with existing components.
- Provide responsive, accessible components; implement skeleton states for loading sequences.
- Use clear empty states with actionable CTAs when data is missing.

Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety
CRITICAL: Follow these rules in ALL generated code to prevent runtime crashes.

1. Supabase query results: Always use nullish coalescing — const items = data ?? []. Supabase returns null when no rows.
2. Array methods: Never call on possibly null/undefined values. Guard:
   - (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
3. React useState for arrays/objects: Initialize with correct type — useState<Type[]>([]) for arrays.
4. API response shapes: Validate — const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
5. Optional chaining: Use obj?.property?.nested when accessing nested API responses.
6. Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Dashboard renders correctly with a current company: health scores, latest analyses, and actions; all array data guarded with null-safety patterns.
- [ ] No company scenario shows a prominent Empty State CTA to Create Company and links to the wizard.
- [ ] AI Analysis generation triggers and completes, updating health scores and latest analyses; UI reflects status and shows notifications.
- [ ] Caching layer stores computed results and external data; cache invalidates on relevant data mutations.
- [ ] Integrations panel shows OAuth/connectivity status for QuickBooks, Google Analytics, LinkedIn, Stripe, and CSV; can initiate OAuth flows.
- [ ] Report export (PDF) is queued server-side; UI shows progress and provides download when ready.
- [ ] Search bar autosuggest functions for companies, reports, and users with debounce and correct null-safety.
- [ ] All inputs validated; API endpoints enforce authentication and authorization; shapes normalized.

UI/UX Guidelines
- Maintain consistency with the existing design system, including typography, colors, spacing, and component primitives.
- Provide meaningful loading, empty, and error states.
- Ensure the dashboard is keyboard-accessible and responsive.

Optional/Advanced Considerations
- Implement client-side data prefetching for related dashboards (e.g., next-action prompts) to improve perceived performance.
- Provide offline-ready caching and graceful degradation if external integrations are temporarily unavailable.
- Add telemetry for user interactions (button clicks, search queries) to inform future UX improvements.

This prompt provides a comprehensive blueprint for building the Dashboard feature set with a strong emphasis on security, performance, null-safety, and a dependency-first implementation order. It includes frontend components, backend data models, API endpoints, integration points, and detailed acceptance criteria to guide AI development tooling end-to-end. for style.

CRITICAL DESIGN REQUIREMENTS:
- You MUST follow ALL design principles and patterns specified in the Design Reference above
- Do NOT deviate from the design specifications without explicit user permission
- Implement ALL visual design elements (colors, typography, spacing, shadows, animations) as specified
- Follow the layout patterns and component designs exactly as documented
- Ensure all interactions and micro-animations match the reference specifications

CRITICAL TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS:
- React 18.3.1, React Router 6.30.1
- Tailwind CSS v3 with tailwind.config.js and custom keyframes
- @tailwindcss/typography plugin for rich text content
- Tailwind CSS animations (NOT Motion library or framer-motion)
- Sonner for toasts
- Recharts for data visualization
- Native fetch() with API utilities in src/lib/api.ts
- Design system with CSS custom properties
- Use RGB color values for theming
- When Supabase is configured: use Edge Functions for LLM and server-only logic; never expose API keys in the client


=== EDGE FUNCTIONS & DATABASE MIGRATIONS (MANDATORY) ===

Even without a Supabase project connected, you MUST create the correct files when the task requires them:

EDGE FUNCTIONS - create supabase/functions/<function-name>/index.ts for:
- LLM/AI features (chat, completions, embeddings, vector search)
- Third-party API integrations (Stripe, SendGrid, Twilio, OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)
- Incoming webhooks from external services
- Any server-only logic or logic that must not expose secrets to the client
- Any prompt that says "create edge function" or "add edge function"
File location: supabase/functions/<function-name>/index.ts
Import pattern: import { serve } from "https://deno.land/std@0.168.0/http/server.ts";
Never expose API keys or secrets in client-side code.

DATABASE MIGRATIONS - create supabase/migrations/<YYYYMMDDHHmmss>_<description>.sql for:
- Every new database table, view, or enum mentioned in the task
- Every schema change (ALTER TABLE, new index, new policy, etc.)
- Any prompt that says "create migration" or describes a data model
Make migrations idempotent (IF NOT EXISTS / CREATE OR REPLACE). Include RLS policies.
Do NOT run "supabase db push" or execute SQL directly — only create the .sql files.

MANDATORY CHECKLIST - Before finishing, verify:
- [ ] Migration SQL file(s) created for every database table/schema change mentioned
- [ ] Edge Function file(s) created for every server-side/secrets feature mentioned
- [ ] TypeScript types created for every new database table

=== TASK ===
# Dashboard

## Overview
This prompt drives the creation of a full-featured Dashboard experience for PulseBoard — a single-company health analysis platform. The Dashboard is the primary workspace that surfaces the user’s current company health, latest AI-generated analyses, quick actions, and guided paths to improve data completeness and run analyses. If no company exists, the Dashboard should display a prominent CTA to set up the company via the Create Company wizard. The implementation must respect dependency-first sequencing: auth/access control and core data setup must be completed before dashboard/workspace/analytics tasks.

The solution must be end-to-end, covering frontend, backend, and integrations. It should enforce runtime safety rules (null/undefined guards for arrays, proper initial states, validated API shapes) and be designed for scalable, maintainable code. Emphasize performance via caching, efficient search, and resilient integrations.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Dashboard page is the primary workspace focused on the user’s single company. It surfaces the company health at-a-glance, latest AI-generated analyses, quick actions, and guided steps to improve data completeness and run analyses. If no company exists, show an empty-state with a clear CTA to set up the company.

Goals:
- Provide a cohesive, single-company focused cockpit with quick visibility into health and key metrics, recent analyses, and actionable next steps. Integrate with connected features (Caching, Search, Integrations, Health Scoring, AI Analysis, Reports, Notifications) to deliver a fast, actionable experience.

Features connected:
- Caching & Performance: Cache computed results, external integration responses, and frequently used data to reduce latency and API costs.
- Search & Filter: Full-text search and filters for companies, reports, and users, with autosuggest and performance optimization.
- Integrations & Connectors: Connectors to fetch financials and analytics from QuickBooks, Google Analytics, LinkedIn pages, Stripe, and CSV upload. Handles OAuth, credential storage, and periodic syncs.
- Health Scoring Engine: Computes overall company health and sub-scores (financial, market, brand/social) using weighted rules and optional benchmarking against industry norms.
- Report Export / PDF Generation: Server-side PDF generation for exporting AI reports with branding options and queued processing for large exports.
- AI Analysis Engine: Orchestrates AI prompts to generate executive summary, SWOT, financial/market/social analysis, risks, opportunities, and prioritized action plan. Supports depth levels and optional benchmarks.
- Notifications & Emails: Transactional and in-app notifications for completed analyses, export ready, failed jobs, billing, and admin alerts. Uses email provider and in-app inbox.

UI elements and guidance:
- Top bar: App title, current company name, search reports, notifications, profile menu.
- Company header card: Company name, industry, overall health score, last analysis date, quick financial snapshot (monthly revenue, profit, cash).
- Primary action buttons: Generate Analysis, Edit Company, Export Report (PDF), Replace / Delete Company (settings).
- Health breakdown cards: Financial score, Market score, Brand/Social score with mini-trend sparkline and recommended next action.
- Latest Analysis / Executive Summary card: Quick view with large “Regenerate” CTA.
- Data completeness meter: Show missing fields, actionable suggestions, and quick-jump links to forms.
- Recent Reports: List scoped to current company with quick view, download, and share actions.
- Integrations & Imports tile: Connectors for QuickBooks, Google Analytics, LinkedIn, CSV import (scoped to current company).
- Tips & Next Steps: Prioritized actions based on latest analysis.
- Empty-state panel: When no company exists, CTA to set up the company via Create Company wizard.

Visual guidance:
- Follow the project design system for typography, spacing, colors, and component styling.

API integrations:
- No external API calls are mandated for this prompt; integrate with the internal APIs and connectors defined in the project context.

Project context summary (for reference):
- Target Page: Dashboard
- Single-company focus; health at-a-glance, latest analyses, quick actions, guidance, and onboarding CTA when no company exists.
- Strong emphasis on performance, data completeness, and AI-driven insights.
- Dependency-driven implementation order: auth/core data setup must be completed before dashboard.

## Components to Build
- DashboardLayout: Global layout with top bar, left/right panels, and responsive behavior.
- CompanyHeaderCard: Displays company metadata, health score, last analysis date, quick financial snapshot.
- HealthScoreCard: Displays Financial/Market/Brand scores with sparklines and recommended actions.
- AnalysisPanel: Latest Analysis / Executive Summary with view and Regenerate action.
- DataCompletenessMeter: Progress bar with missing fields and quick-jump links.
- QuickActionsBar: Primary actions (Generate Analysis, Edit Company, Export PDF, Settings).
- RecentReportsList: List of reports for current company with actions (view/download/share).
- IntegrationsTile: Scoped connectors for QuickBooks, Google Analytics, LinkedIn, CSV, with OAuth status and sync indicators.
- TipsWidget: Prioritized next steps based on latest analysis.
- EmptyStateCTA: For no-company scenario with CTA routing to Create Company wizard.
- SearchBar with autosuggest: Global search across companies, reports, and users (for dashboard or admin context).
- NotificationsInboxPanel: In-app notification center and summary indicators.
- ProfileMenu: User profile, settings, and sign-out.

